<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<%- include('/partials/head') %>
</head>
<body>

<%- include('/partials/header') %>

<section class="page-hero about">
  <div class="copy">
    <h1>An origin, <em>a lineage</em>, a living temple.</h1>
    <div class="jp-line">寺院縁起と住職紹介　—　ABOUT</div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- The School -->
<section class="blk" id="school">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <div class="eyebrow-wrap"><span class="eyebrow">I — The School</span></div>
      <div>
        <h2>What is <em>Nichiren-shū</em>?</h2>
        <p class="lead">One of the major schools of Japanese Buddhism, founded in the 13th century by Nichiren Shōnin. Its practice centres on the Lotus Sūtra and the mantra Namu Myōhō Renge Kyō.</p>
        <div class="jp-sub">日蓮宗とは</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="school-grid">
      <div class="school-body">
        <p>Nichiren-shū holds that the Lotus Sūtra — the teaching the historical Buddha is said to have preserved as his final and most essential — contains the complete truth of Buddhism, and that this teaching is especially intended for the present age.</p>
        <p>The school centres practice on three cardinal observances (三大秘法): the Object of Veneration (本門の本尊), the Sacred Title chanted as Namu Myōhō Renge Kyō (本門の題目), and the Sanctuary of ordination (本門の戒壇). Through chanting, study, and daily conduct, practitioners aspire to awaken to the Buddha within themselves and to manifest a Buddha-land in the world as it is.</p>
        <div class="pull">"Practice and study arise from faith. If you have the strength, speak — <em>even a single phrase, a single line.</em>"</div>
        <p>Nichiren-shū remains a community of lay followers and ordained clergy bound by the founder's injunction — unsparing of life (不惜身命), united in heart though different in body (異体同心) — and oriented always toward the head mountain at Kuonji on Mt. Minobu.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="school-facts">
        <dl>
          <div class="row"><dt>Head temple</dt><dd>Kuonji, Mt. Minobu<span class="jp">総本山　身延山久遠寺 — 山梨県</span></dd></div>
          <div class="row"><dt>Object of<br>veneration</dt><dd>The Great Mandala (Dai-Mandara)<span class="jp">ご本尊　大曼荼羅御本尊</span></dd></div>
          <div class="row"><dt>Founder</dt><dd>Nichiren Shōnin (1222–1282)<span class="jp">開祖　日蓮大聖人</span></dd></div>
          <div class="row"><dt>Temples</dt><dd><span class="num">5,101</span>nationwide<br><span class="asof">As of 1 Jan 2024</span></dd></div>
          <div class="row"><dt>Clergy</dt><dd><span class="num">7,567</span>ordained priests<br><span class="asof">As of 1 Jan 2024</span></dd></div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Head Priest -->
<section class="blk" id="priest">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <div class="eyebrow-wrap"><span class="eyebrow">II — Head Priest</span></div>
      <div>
        <h2>The <em>fifth</em> abbot of Myohokkein.</h2>
        <p class="lead">The temple is led today by Rev. Shinma Chikō, who inherited the Dharma Lamp in 2011 as the fifth-generation abbot.</p>
        <div class="jp-sub">住職紹介</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="priest">
      <div class="photo">
        <div class="placeholder">
          <span class="placeholder-note">PORTRAIT<br>Rev. Shinma Chikō<br>tikou.jpg</span>
        </div>
        <span class="cap">新間 智孝 住職</span>
      </div>
      <div class="priest-body">
        <div class="title-tag">Fifth-generation abbot</div>
        <h3>Rev. Shinma Chikō</h3>
        <div class="romaji">Shinma Chikō · 1963 —</div>
        <div class="jp-name">新間 智孝（しんま ちこう）</div>
        <div class="bio">
          <p>Born in Wakayama City in December 1963; raised from infancy in Kobe, on the grounds of Myohokkein after being taken in by the Shinma family. Trained in the classical curriculum of Nichiren-shū at Risshō University and ordained at Hokkekyō-ji's Great Ascetic Hall (大荒行堂), which he completed twice.</p>
          <div class="quote">"When the Great Hanshin Earthquake came, I was standing at its centre — and it remade how I understood the question, <em>what is faith for?</em>"
            <div class="quote-jp">—— 平成7年　阪神・淡路大震災の経験より</div>
          </div>
          <p>After the 1995 earthquake, Rev. Shinma spent half a year at Mt. Minobu re-studying the Lotus Sūtra and the founder's writings from the beginning. He later served as a local fire-brigade volunteer, edited an earthquake-memorial volume, ran the regional Nichiren-shū newspaper bureau, and worked in the denomination's Kinki-region administration before assuming the abbacy here in 2011.</p>
        </div>
        <dl class="timeline-years">
          <div class="row"><dt>1963 · Dec<span class="era">Shōwa 38</span></dt><dd>Born in Wakayama City. Father Yamasaki Yoshihiro passed away that August; adopted in March 1964 into the Shinma family in Kobe.</dd></div>
          <div class="row"><dt>1978<span class="era">Shōwa 53</span></dt><dd>Becomes a disciple of his adoptive uncle, Rev. Shinma Chishō, the fourth abbot.</dd></div>
          <div class="row"><dt>1982<span class="era">Shōwa 57</span></dt><dd>Graduates Kobe Shinkō High School. Formally ordained (tokudo).</dd></div>
          <div class="row"><dt>1986<span class="era">Shōwa 61</span></dt><dd>Graduates Risshō University, Faculty of Buddhist Studies. Completes the Great Ascetic Hall at Nakayama Hokkekyō-ji a second time.</dd></div>
          <div class="row"><dt>2011 · Nov<span class="era">Heisei 22</span></dt><dd>Inherits the Dharma Lamp as the fifth-generation abbot of Myohokkein.</dd></div>
        </dl>
        <div class="credentials">
          <h4>Qualifications &amp; roles</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Specialist Propagator (布教専修師)</li>
            <li>Ritual Master (修法師)</li>
            <li>Social Educator (社会教導師)</li>
            <li>Spiritual Counsellor (霊断師)</li>
            <li>President, Hyōgo East Propagators' Society</li>
            <li>Editorial Committee, Nichiren-shū Shimbun</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="cta">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="cta-grid">
      <a class="cta-card" href="<%= rootPath %>#access">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Plan a visit</span>
          <h3>Open daily, 7:00 — 17:00.</h3>
          <p>A fifteen-minute walk from Shin-Kobe Station. All are welcome during open hours — no reservation required.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="arrow">Access &amp; hours</span>
      </a>
      <a class="cta-card image" href="<%= rootPath %>#social">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Follow along</span>
          <h3>Ceremonies, live and recorded.</h3>
          <p>Five- to ten-minute films of each observance on YouTube; quiet moments from the grounds on Instagram.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="arrow">Instagram &amp; YouTube</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include('/partials/footer') %>

<script src="<%= rootPath %>site.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
